docs.snippet: A report from the nonpartisan New American Leaders Project, which is focused on getting more Asian-American and Latinos elected to state and local offices, found that the fast-growing groups are facing obstacles as they seek to achieve greater rep...
docs.abstract: A report from the nonpartisan New American Leaders Project, which is focused on getting more Asian-American and Latinos elected to state and local offices, found that the fast-growing groups are facing obstacles as they seek to achieve greater representation.

headline.main: Hispanics and Asian-Americans Face Barriers to Lower Offices, Report Finds

docs.snippet: About 300 people gathered in Cairo's Tahrir Square on Monday, not to celebrate the instigators of the revolt that five years ago overthrew Egypt's longtime ruler Hosni Mubarak but to praise the police who tried to stop them....
docs.lead_paragraph: About 300 people gathered in Cairo's Tahrir Square on Monday, not to celebrate the instigators of the revolt that five years ago overthrew Egypt's longtime ruler Hosni Mubarak but to praise the police who tried to stop them.

headline.main: Five Years After Egypt Uprising, Police -- Not Activists -- Celebrated
headline.print_headline: Five Years After Egypt Uprising, Police -- Not Activists -- Celebrated
